♪ She stumbled onto the scene ♪

1730
01:22:21.399 --> 01:22:24.345
♪ Billie Jean
is not my lover. ♪

1731
01:22:24.369 --> 01:22:27.568
-(music fades)
-(cheering. shouting)

1732
01:22:30.771 --> 01:22:33.508
(cheering fades)

1733
01:22:34.984 --> 01:22:38.579
-(indistinct chatter)
-(camera shutters clicking)

1734
01:22:40.550 --> 01:22:43.716
MAN: Mr. Gordy.
Mr. Gordy. over here.

1735
01:22:44.158 --> 01:22:45.003
Where is he?

1736
01:22:45.027 --> 01:22:46.939
There he is. There he is.
Come on.

1737
01:22:46.963 --> 01:22:49.403
Are you kidding me?
That was brilliant. Michael.

1738
01:22:49.427 --> 01:22:51.702
Oh. you shook the world
with that performance.

1739
01:22:51.726 --> 01:22:52.604
Oh. my goodness.

1740
01:22:52.628 --> 01:22:54.045
I was supposed to stay
on my toes longer.

1741
01:22:54.069 --> 01:22:55.541
SUZANNE:
Michael. I'm so proud of you.

1742
01:22:55.565 --> 01:22:56.773
Everyone is talking about it.

1743
01:22:56.797 --> 01:22:58.379
-(Katherine squeals happily)
-(Joseph laughing)

1744
01:22:58.403 --> 01:22:59.985
JOSEPH: Y'all see that
out there tonight?

1745
01:23:00.009 --> 01:23:01.646
-Y'all see that?
-(Katherine speaks indistinctly)

1746
01:23:01.670 --> 01:23:03.714
Oh. come on.
y'all did your thang!

1747
01:23:03.738 --> 01:23:06.123
That's my son. That's my son.

1748
01:23:06.147 --> 01:23:09.555
A regular moneymaking machine.
(chuckles)

1749
01:23:09.579 --> 01:23:11.997
-Hey. we'll catch you later. Mike.
-MICHAEL: Yeah.

1750
01:23:12.021 --> 01:23:15.682
-Yeah. bye. Mike.
-It's okay. Mother.

1751
01:23:17.323 --> 01:23:20.434
Just couldn't give him
one night. huh?

1752
01:23:20.458 --> 01:23:22.007
(Tito scoffs)

1753
01:23:22.031 --> 01:23:23.536
JOSEPH:
What?

1754
01:23:23.560 --> 01:23:25.274
(laughs softly)

1755
01:23:25.298 --> 01:23:28.838
JOSEPH: <i>So. now
let me get this straight. Don.</i>

1756
01:23:28.862 --> 01:23:29.773
<i>Ten. 11 or 12?</i>

1757
01:23:29.797 --> 01:23:31.346
How many wins do you have?
You. uh...

1758
01:23:31.370 --> 01:23:35.944
That's 13 of the current world
champions that I've promoted.

1759
01:23:35.968 --> 01:23:38.947
We got 110 fighters
in our stable right now.

1760
01:23:38.971 --> 01:23:41.026
But I'm gonna
tell you this. all right?

1761
01:23:41.050 --> 01:23:44.755
The big business
that's gonna be booming?

1762
01:23:44.779 --> 01:23:45.855
The lightweight class.

1763
01:23:45.879 --> 01:23:49.100
I'm gonna take those young
stars all the way to the top.

1764
01:23:49.124 --> 01:23:50.563
-Yeah. you are. (laughs)
-Yeah.

1765
01:23:50.587 --> 01:23:53.962
-Life is good. my friend.
-Yes. it is.

1766
01:23:53.986 --> 01:23:55.238
-(both laughing)
-Yes. it is.

1767
01:23:55.262 --> 01:23:57.603
Those Cubans.
straight from Castro himself.

1768
01:23:57.627 --> 01:23:58.769
-All right. (sniffs)
-Yes.

1769
01:23:58.793 --> 01:24:01.970
-Yes. yes. yes. yes.
-Oh. yes.

1770
01:24:01.994 --> 01:24:03.147
Now...

1771
01:24:03.171 --> 01:24:06.535
what did you want
to talk to me about?

1772
01:24:08.704 --> 01:24:11.716
Have you thought about getting
into the music business?

1773
01:24:11.740 --> 01:24:16.380
-Crossover-type thing?
-I don't follow you.

1774
01:24:16.481 --> 01:24:18.162
Well. I'm about to take

1775
01:24:18.186 --> 01:24:19.559
-my boys on a world tour.
-Hmm.

1776
01:24:19.583 --> 01:24:21.561
You know. we're gonna start
with North America.

1777
01:24:21.585 --> 01:24:23.497
-You know. stadiums only.
-Hmm.

1778
01:24:23.521 --> 01:24:24.663
You know. the biggest.

1779
01:24:24.687 --> 01:24:27.501
It's time to show the world
that the Jacksons are back.

1780
01:24:27.525 --> 01:24:29.536
-Right on. Okay.
-And bigger than ever.

1781
01:24:29.560 --> 01:24:31.538
You've seen them sales
on <i>Thriller.</i>

1782
01:24:31.562 --> 01:24:32.539
-Huh?
-Mm-hmm.

1783
01:24:32.563 --> 01:24:34.376
People are gonna be
climbing the walls.

1784
01:24:34.400 --> 01:24:37.104
(both laughing)

1785
01:24:37.304 --> 01:24:40.140
Is Michael gonna be there?

1786
01:24:41.572 --> 01:24:42.978
(lighter snaps shut)

1787
01:24:43.002 --> 01:24:45.013
Of course Michael's
gonna be there.

1788
01:24:45.037 --> 01:24:47.719
Hmm. That's good to hear.

1789
01:24:47.743 --> 01:24:50.711
Now. what's in it for me?

1790
01:24:52.385 --> 01:24:53.725
I've been watching you. Don.

1791
01:24:53.749 --> 01:24:55.727
-I watch you like a hawk.
-Hmm. (chuckles)

1792
01:24:55.751 --> 01:24:58.268
I love the way
you promote your fighters.

1793
01:24:58.292 --> 01:25:00.237
-Uh-huh.
-You're the king of marketing.

1794
01:25:00.261 --> 01:25:03.141
You know. I just. uh.
I think that you and I.

1795
01:25:03.165 --> 01:25:06.298
if we came together.
we could. uh...

1796
01:25:06.432 --> 01:25:08.608
we could form
a good partnership.

1797
01:25:08.632 --> 01:25:09.807
Me and you?

1798
01:25:09.831 --> 01:25:11.578
I'll cut you a good deal.

1799
01:25:11.602 --> 01:25:15.472
-I like deals.
-(sets down lighter)

1800
01:25:20.908 --> 01:25:22.589
I need...

1801
01:25:22.613 --> 01:25:24.844
this for my boys.

1802
01:25:24.978 --> 01:25:25.922
I need it.

1803
01:25:25.946 --> 01:25:28.727
You know. I-I think
they deserve the-the...

1804
01:25:28.751 --> 01:25:30.025
Rolls-Royce of sponsorships.

1805
01:25:30.049 --> 01:25:33.402
I mean. merchandising.
marketing. you hear me?

1806
01:25:33.426 --> 01:25:34.898
I mean. it's got to be huge.

1807
01:25:34.922 --> 01:25:38.627
And only you and I could do it.

1808
01:25:38.728 --> 01:25:40.607
It'll be called...

1809
01:25:40.631 --> 01:25:44.006
-the Victory tour.
-Hmm.

1810
01:25:44.030 --> 01:25:46.008
(sucks teeth)

1811
01:25:46.032 --> 01:25:47.548
(clicks tongue)

1812
01:25:47.572 --> 01:25:49.847
I may have something for you.

1813
01:25:49.871 --> 01:25:50.749
Pepsi.

1814
01:25:50.773 --> 01:25:52.916
They want to get
back in the game.

1815
01:25:52.940 --> 01:25:55.292
Michael could be
the face of the brand.

1816
01:25:55.316 --> 01:25:57.052
do some commercials.

1817
01:25:57.076 --> 01:25:59.296
-All right.
-(chuckles)

1818
01:25:59.320 --> 01:26:01.914
-I can see it.
-Yeah.

1819
01:26:02.290 --> 01:26:04.598
But you wouldn't be
bullshitting me.

1820
01:26:04.622 --> 01:26:06.402
would you. Joe?

1821
01:26:06.426 --> 01:26:10.791
'Cause if you
can't get Michael...

1822
01:26:13.697 --> 01:26:16.830
<i>(dramatic music playing on TV)</i>

1823
01:26:19.670 --> 01:26:20.746
(Katherine laughing)

1824
01:26:20.770 --> 01:26:24.640
Now. that... now. that's
my favorite part. (laughs)

1825
01:26:29.548 --> 01:26:31.922
I'm gonna
leave it to you. Michael.

1826
01:26:31.946 --> 01:26:32.956
You can't go yet.

1827
01:26:32.980 --> 01:26:34.463
No.
I'm going to bed. I'm tired.

1828
01:26:34.487 --> 01:26:36.531
You got to stay for the ending.
That's the best part.

1829
01:26:36.555 --> 01:26:39.171
Your mother is tired. baby.

1830
01:26:39.195 --> 01:26:42.240
Do me a favor. Make sure
you turn the lights off?

1831
01:26:42.264 --> 01:26:44.374
-Night. Mother.
-Good night.

1832
01:26:44.398 --> 01:26:47.157
(music continues on TV)

1833
01:26:48.930 --> 01:26:50.281
(chuckles)

1834
01:26:50.305 --> 01:26:53.130
(humming softly)

1835
01:26:54.243 --> 01:26:56.507
(switch clicks)

1836
01:26:56.971 --> 01:26:58.817
(humming continues)

1837
01:26:58.841 --> 01:27:01.842
(vocalizing softly)

1838
01:27:12.987 --> 01:27:15.306
(vocalizing continues)

1839
01:27:15.330 --> 01:27:17.121
(gasps)

1840
01:27:19.862 --> 01:27:22.577
Why are you here?

1841
01:27:22.601 --> 01:27:26.031
What? Can't a father
visit his son?

1842
01:27:27.166 --> 01:27:30.145
Biggest-selling record
of all time.

1843
01:27:30.169 --> 01:27:32.884
from a poor kid from Gary.

1844
01:27:32.908 --> 01:27:35.414
Who would have thought?

1845
01:27:35.647 --> 01:27:38.230
Me. I thought.

1846
01:27:38.254 --> 01:27:40.782
(chuckles)

1847
01:27:43.457 --> 01:27:45.655
Come here.

1848
01:27:45.756 --> 01:27:48.889
Joseph. I know
you want something.

1849
01:27:53.093 --> 01:27:55.203
Michael...

1850
01:27:55.227 --> 01:27:59.306
I'm gonna need you
to tour with your brothers.

1851
01:27:59.407 --> 01:28:02.947
Now. I let you do
that album by yourself.

1852
01:28:02.971 --> 01:28:06.236
I'm gonna need you
to do this for me.

1853
01:28:07.382 --> 01:28:09.481
For your family.

1854
01:28:09.582 --> 01:28:12.187
I'm not a child anymore. Joseph.

1855
01:28:12.211 --> 01:28:13.122
(sighs heavily)

1856
01:28:13.146 --> 01:28:14.728
-And you're not my manager.
-Here we go.

1857
01:28:14.752 --> 01:28:17.951
I have to start
living my own life.

1858
01:28:18.822 --> 01:28:21.119
On my own.

1859
01:28:21.297 --> 01:28:22.901
Just like everyone else.

1860
01:28:22.925 --> 01:28:25.761
You ain't like everyone else.

1861
01:28:26.566 --> 01:28:28.170
So. you're trying to tell me

1862
01:28:28.194 --> 01:28:31.635
you want to be treated
like an adult?

1863
01:28:32.000 --> 01:28:32.878
All right.

1864
01:28:32.902 --> 01:28:37.454
You want to
see what the world is like...

1865
01:28:37.478 --> 01:28:40.688
without a family
that protects you.

1866
01:28:40.712 --> 01:28:42.217
(hinges creaking)

1867
01:28:42.241 --> 01:28:44.593
Without a family that...

1868
01:28:44.617 --> 01:28:46.364
understands you.

1869
01:28:46.388 --> 01:28:49.598
Nobody else will understand you
outside this place.

1870
01:28:49.622 --> 01:28:52.964
There you'll be with
all the money in the world.

1871
01:28:52.988 --> 01:28:56.165
surrounded by people
who'll say "yes"

1872
01:28:56.189 --> 01:28:59.157
to everything.

1873
01:29:00.094 --> 01:29:03.161
Is that what you want?

1874
01:29:05.572 --> 01:29:08.342
What kind of sense that make?

1875
01:29:14.977 --> 01:29:17.428
I'm gonna...

1876
01:29:17.452 --> 01:29:18.627
call Don King

1877
01:29:18.651 --> 01:29:22.312
and tell him
you're doing the tour.

1878
01:29:23.051 --> 01:29:26.987
I know you don't want
to let your family down.

1879
01:29:28.859 --> 01:29:31.860
(Michael breathing deeply)

1880
01:29:34.601 --> 01:29:37.030
(door closes)

1881
01:29:37.637 --> 01:29:40.330
♪♪

1882
01:29:45.480 --> 01:29:47.546
(sighs)

1883
01:29:48.846 --> 01:29:50.219
(crowd cheering loudly)

1884
01:29:50.243 --> 01:29:53.684
("Billie Jean" playing)

1885
01:29:56.887 --> 01:29:59.195
♪ You're a whole
new generation ♪

1886
01:29:59.219 --> 01:30:01.505
♪ You're lovin' what you do ♪

1887
01:30:01.529 --> 01:30:03.298
♪ Put a Pepsi in the motion ♪

1888
01:30:03.322 --> 01:30:04.937
♪ That choice is up to you.
hey-ey ♪

1889
01:30:04.961 --> 01:30:07.203
-DIRECTOR: Cut! Cut! Cut! Cut!
-♪ You're the Pepsi... ♪

1890
01:30:07.227 --> 01:30:09.744
-(music stops)
-MAN: We're cutting. guys.

1891
01:30:09.768 --> 01:30:14.111
All right. here's what I need.
I'm thinking...

1892
01:30:14.135 --> 01:30:16.949
I'm gonna move the camera in
while you're up here.

1893
01:30:16.973 --> 01:30:20.216
I need to get a close-up
of you at the top.

1894
01:30:20.240 --> 01:30:22.251
so just feel the camera
as you come down.

1895
01:30:22.275 --> 01:30:24.319
-Okay.
-Okay. great. All right.

1896
01:30:24.343 --> 01:30:25.727
DIRECTOR:
Okay. everybody.

1897
01:30:25.751 --> 01:30:26.695
(grunts) Here we go.

1898
01:30:26.719 --> 01:30:29.599
What is this?
What do we got. take six?

1899
01:30:29.623 --> 01:30:32.063
-(groans quietly)
-Lucky six. Lucky six.

1900
01:30:32.087 --> 01:30:33.405
Here we go. Energy. everybody!

1901
01:30:33.429 --> 01:30:36.408
You love the Jacksons.
You love the Jacksons.

1902
01:30:36.432 --> 01:30:38.267
You love Pepsi. Let's go!

1903
01:30:38.291 --> 01:30:40.874
-WOMAN: A marker!
-(marker snaps)

1904
01:30:40.898 --> 01:30:42.172
-MAN 2: B mark!
-(marker snaps)

1905
01:30:42.196 --> 01:30:43.910
-MAN 3: C mark.
-(audience cheering)

1906
01:30:43.934 --> 01:30:46.209
-(marker snaps)
-DIRECTOR: And playback.

1907
01:30:46.233 --> 01:30:50.301
("Billie Jean" playing)

1908
01:30:52.404 --> 01:30:55.141
(fireworks explode)

1909
01:31:03.657 --> 01:31:05.536
-(music fades)
-(sizzling)

1910
01:31:05.560 --> 01:31:06.801
(muffled cheering)

1911
01:31:06.825 --> 01:31:09.166
(distorted whimpering)

1912
01:31:09.190 --> 01:31:12.257
(distorted moaning)

1913
01:31:12.600 --> 01:31:14.611
-(music resumes)
-(screaming)

1914
01:31:14.635 --> 01:31:15.271
Cut it.

1915
01:31:15.295 --> 01:31:17.515
-MAN: Put it out!
-(Michael groaning)

1916
01:31:17.539 --> 01:31:18.582
(microphone feedback)

1917
01:31:18.606 --> 01:31:20.408
-(groaning)
-TITO: Michael!

1918
01:31:20.432 --> 01:31:22.179
-(clamoring. screaming)
-(groaning)

1919
01:31:22.203 --> 01:31:23.785
-What happened?
-(moaning)

1920
01:31:23.809 --> 01:31:25.688
-BILL: Back up. back up. back up.
-Bill. get him out of here.

1921
01:31:25.712 --> 01:31:28.053
BILL: I'm here. I'm here.
I'm here. Michael.

1922
01:31:28.077 --> 01:31:29.989
-Get him up. get him up.
-I'm here. Joker. I'm here.

1923
01:31:30.013 --> 01:31:32.288
Hey. you're gonna be okay.
okay? You're gonna be okay.

1924
01:31:32.312 --> 01:31:33.960
BILL:
Come on. Mike. Clear a path!

1925
01:31:33.984 --> 01:31:36.798
(people screaming and clamoring)

1926
01:31:36.822 --> 01:31:40.197
Out of my way!
Michael. I'm coming!

1927
01:31:40.221 --> 01:31:42.034
-(moans)
-Get back! Get out of my way!

1928
01:31:42.058 --> 01:31:45.499
Clear a path!
Get back! Get back!

1929
01:31:45.666 --> 01:31:49.074
Clear a path!
Move! Move. please!

1930
01:31:49.098 --> 01:31:51.879
(muffled shouting and wailing)

1931
01:31:51.903 --> 01:31:54.640
BILL:
Excuse me!

1932
01:31:54.972 --> 01:31:56.785
(whimpering)

1933
01:31:56.809 --> 01:31:59.513
♪♪

1934
01:32:06.379 --> 01:32:08.423
(phone ringing)

1935
01:32:08.447 --> 01:32:10.480
(Joseph exhales)

1936
01:32:10.790 --> 01:32:13.857
(continues tapping fingers)

1937
01:32:16.532 --> 01:32:19.698
(indistinct P.A. announcement)

1938
01:32:23.671 --> 01:32:26.463
Hey. Kate. come on.

1939
01:32:27.609 --> 01:32:28.751
Hey. I need to talk to you.

1940
01:32:28.775 --> 01:32:30.852
-Sir.
-I'm his father. Joseph Jackson.

1941
01:32:30.876 --> 01:32:32.216
This is his mother. Katherine.

1942
01:32:32.240 --> 01:32:35.153
-Hi. It's good to meet you.
-Very nice to meet you.

1943
01:32:35.177 --> 01:32:35.923
Thank you.

1944
01:32:35.947 --> 01:32:37.694
Well. your son is
in stable condition.

1945
01:32:37.718 --> 01:32:39.124
-All right.
-DOCTOR: All right?

1946
01:32:39.148 --> 01:32:42.325
And. uh. we're trying to bring
his heart rate down.

1947
01:32:42.349 --> 01:32:45.086
but he's in a lot of pain.

1948
01:32:45.385 --> 01:32:46.868
Okay. When will he recover?

1949
01:32:46.892 --> 01:32:48.100
It's too soon to tell.

1950
01:32:48.124 --> 01:32:49.970
It's gonna be
a long road. all right?

1951
01:32:49.994 --> 01:32:55.096
He has third-degree burns
and substantial nerve damage.

1952
01:32:55.428 --> 01:32:57.406
JOSEPH:
Okay.

1953
01:32:57.430 --> 01:33:01.377
Do you think he'll ever be
able to perform again?

1954
01:33:01.401 --> 01:33:02.620
Ever?

1955
01:33:02.644 --> 01:33:05.073
KATHERINE:
Joseph.

1956
01:33:06.648 --> 01:33:10.925
Mr. Jackson.
your son almost died.

1957
01:33:10.949 --> 01:33:11.893
I know that.

1958
01:33:11.917 --> 01:33:13.422
Well. if that fire
had caught his clothes.

1959
01:33:13.446 --> 01:33:17.261
or burned over to his face
and eyes. he wouldn't be here.

1960
01:33:17.285 --> 01:33:18.328
I know my boy.

1961
01:33:18.352 --> 01:33:20.803
And the only thing
that's gonna heal him

1962
01:33:20.827 --> 01:33:23.454
is by getting
back on that stage.

1963
01:33:23.962 --> 01:33:25.170
That's where he lives.

1964
01:33:25.194 --> 01:33:26.875
-DOCTOR: I understand that. sir.
-LA TOYA: Oh. my God.

1965
01:33:26.899 --> 01:33:28.646
-But it's gonna be a while.
-Do you? All right.

1966
01:33:28.670 --> 01:33:30.505
DOCTOR:
Yes. I do. But. Mr. Jackson...

1967
01:33:30.529 --> 01:33:34.476
he's gonna need
your support to get there.

1968
01:33:34.500 --> 01:33:36.808
I'm sorry.

1969
01:33:38.570 --> 01:33:40.218
(exhales)

1970
01:33:40.242 --> 01:33:42.022
WOMAN (shouting in distance):
Praying for you. Michael!

1971
01:33:42.046 --> 01:33:44.387
DOCTOR: It's unlikely
that will grow back.

1972
01:33:44.411 --> 01:33:47.830
You'll need surgery
to laser the scar tissue

1973
01:33:47.854 --> 01:33:51.229
and stretch part of the scalp
over the burn.

1974
01:33:51.253 --> 01:33:55.035
All right? We'll insert an
implant to protect the scalp.

1975
01:33:55.059 --> 01:33:57.169
Will I have to wear a wig?

1976
01:33:57.193 --> 01:33:59.930
Well. right there on top.

1977
01:34:00.900 --> 01:34:04.011
What kind of wig?
Like. a full wig?

1978
01:34:04.035 --> 01:34:04.979
Hard to say.

1979
01:34:05.003 --> 01:34:06.684
There are prosthetic
hair weaves we can try.

1980
01:34:06.708 --> 01:34:11.469
but we won't know till we see
how the surgery goes next week.

1981
01:34:13.143 --> 01:34:16.276
(indistinct P.A. announcement)

1982
01:34:16.784 --> 01:34:18.927
(crowd shouting indistinctly
in the distance)

1983
01:34:18.951 --> 01:34:19.961
You'll. um...

1984
01:34:19.985 --> 01:34:22.964
you'll have to stay
on the Demerol for a while.

1985
01:34:22.988 --> 01:34:24.867
I don't want to take medication.

1986
01:34:24.891 --> 01:34:27.166
I have to be honest.
Mr. Jackson.

1987
01:34:27.190 --> 01:34:28.772
you're gonna need them.

1988
01:34:28.796 --> 01:34:31.533
We have to replace
the implant periodically.

1989
01:34:31.557 --> 01:34:33.645
The nerves are exposed up there.

1990
01:34:33.669 --> 01:34:36.527
You'll be in a lot of pain.

1991
01:34:37.805 --> 01:34:42.038
I'll let you rest.
but I'll be back later.

1992
01:34:46.011 --> 01:34:49.056
WOMAN: We'll stay here
till you're better. Michael!

1993
01:34:49.080 --> 01:34:50.486
REPORTER:
You see the number of people

1994
01:34:50.510 --> 01:34:53.159
who have already gathered
outside the hospital.

1995
01:34:53.183 --> 01:34:54.259
If that isn't a testament

1996
01:34:54.283 --> 01:34:56.327
to the star power
of Michael Jackson.

1997
01:34:56.351 --> 01:34:57.427
I don't know what is.

1998
01:34:57.451 --> 01:34:59.770
Say they won't go back
until Jackson is all right.

1999
01:34:59.794 --> 01:35:02.861
-(donkey braying on TV)
-(door opens)

2000
01:35:03.061 --> 01:35:04.467
All right.

2001
01:35:04.491 --> 01:35:06.139
All right. Joker.

2002
01:35:06.163 --> 01:35:07.338
Got all your favorites.

2003
01:35:07.362 --> 01:35:08.812
-Golden Temple...
-(Katherine laughs)

2004
01:35:08.836 --> 01:35:10.341
-They send their love.
-Golden Temple's

2005
01:35:10.365 --> 01:35:11.848
-your favorite. Michael.
-Got some Mexican.

2006
01:35:11.872 --> 01:35:13.014
Chinese. Some fried chicken.

2007
01:35:13.038 --> 01:35:16.204
Even got these
little red candies you like.

2008
01:35:16.745 --> 01:35:17.986
Thanks. Bill.

2009
01:35:18.010 --> 01:35:20.318
You can just leave it there.

2010
01:35:20.342 --> 01:35:22.507
I'm not hungry.

2011
01:35:22.718 --> 01:35:25.378
Oh. Okay.

2012
01:35:27.283 --> 01:35:28.865
I'll leave you all to it.

2013
01:35:28.889 --> 01:35:32.825
-Okay. Thank you. Bill.
-Mm-hmm.

2014
01:35:40.428 --> 01:35:42.714
(door closes)

2015
01:35:42.738 --> 01:35:45.101
(monitor beeps)

2016
01:35:59.480 --> 01:36:02.085
I'm sorry. Michael.

2017
01:36:05.321 --> 01:36:08.201
I should have protected you.

2018
01:36:08.225 --> 01:36:13.690
Mother. I don't want to
discuss this right now.

2019
01:36:14.066 --> 01:36:16.066
Okay.

2020
01:36:16.398 --> 01:36:18.805
(monitor beeps)

2021
01:36:21.238 --> 01:36:24.074
No one can stop Joseph.

2022
01:36:27.112 --> 01:36:29.112
Nobody.

2023
01:36:35.956 --> 01:36:39.100
You just know that.
no matter what happens.

2024
01:36:39.124 --> 01:36:42.653
I'm gonna be here for you...

2025
01:36:42.963 --> 01:36:45.359
always.

2026
01:36:46.934 --> 01:36:50.034
I should get
some rest now. Mother.

2027
01:37:01.509 --> 01:37:04.345
♪♪

2028
01:37:13.356 --> 01:37:16.093
It's not your fault.

2029
01:37:16.293 --> 01:37:19.096
♪♪

